                        <h2 class="card-title mt-3">VINCENT COLLIARD, Polar Explorer</h2>
                        <p>
                            The word commitment gets thrown around a lot in adventure. French Polar explorer Vincent
                            Colliard is setting a new bar with his aim to ski the 20 largest ice caps over the next 10
                            years. After some impressive expeditions and first ascents in cold and remote places such as
                            the Himalaya and Patagonia, the mountain guide from the Basque country met accomplished
                            Norwegian Polar explorer Børge Ousland. After sailing the Northwest Passage together, they
                            launched Project Ice Legacy in 2014 and have already ticked off five ice caps on the list,
                            including the three biggest, which are all in Alaska.
                            Awareness, of course, is at the heart of Colliard’s mission, as he sees the ice caps as our
                            most fragile and vulnerable ecosystems. As such, he’s teamed up with the scientific
                            community in collecting data from the field that will help us chart how fast the ice is
                            disappearing. One thing is for sure, no one on this planet will know the ice caps quite like
                            Colliard by 2024.
                        </p>
